   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>. . . Artemis . . .  Hieron . . . in planting of cucumbers and melons, fixed [l. 5] rental fees being three hundred silver drachmas, and I will deliver as payment, on a daily basis, from the day of the beginning of the harvesting, 10 cucumbers, 4 melons, 4 gourds in the months of Pauni [l. 10] and Epeiph of the same year, without delay.  The plot of land being public allocated to Horion . . .</ab>
